                                 USBWall

----------- Requirements before installing -----------

Get kernel sources : kernel.org or distributor's kernels sources package
Developed with 
   > Linux Kernel : version 2.6.32-34
   > Distribution : Ubuntu 10.04 LTS (Lucid Lynx) 

----------- Installation -----------
0- Open a linux console

1- Compile the module :
	> go to the "usball" repertory : "cd .../usbwall"
        > run the compilation : "make"

2- Insert the module (whit root permission) :
        > go to the "src" directory : "cd .../usbwall/src"
        > insert the module : "insmod usbwall.ko"

2- Compile & configure the library :
	> go to the "usball_lib" repertory : "cd .../usbwall_lib"
        > rnu configuration : "./configure"
        > run the compilation : "make"
        > install : sudo make install

3- Compile test applications 
        > go to the "usbwall_testapp" directory : cd ../usbwall_testapp
        > run compilation : "make"

4- Create white list : run the create white list application
        > go to the "src" directory : cd ../usbwall_testapp/src
        > run application : "./load_white_liste"

5- Charge white list : run the load white list application
        > run application : "./load_white_liste"
        

(a)- To see usbwall kernel messages 
        > use : dmesg | grep usbwall  

(b)- To remove the usb_storage module (whit root permission) :
	> rmmod usb_storage

(c)- To remove the usbwall module (whit root permission) :
	> rmmod usbwall 

